## 3. Supabase Redirect URL Allowlist

> **Common error**: `"Redirect URL not in allowed list"`
> This occurs when the OAuth callback URL is not explicitly allowed in Supabase.

### Add Redirect URLs

1. Go to [Supabase Dashboard](https://supabase.com/dashboard) > your project
2. Navigate to **Authentication** > **URL Configuration**
3. Under **Redirect URLs**, add:
   - For local development: `http://localhost:3000/**`
   - For production: `https://<your-vercel-domain>/**`
   - For Vercel preview deployments: `https://*-<your-team>.vercel.app/**`

The `**` wildcard matches any path under that domain, which covers the `/auth/callback?returnTo=...` redirect.

---

## 4. Verification Checklist

After completing the setup above:

- [ ] Run `npm run dev` and go to `http://localhost:3000/auth/login`
- [ ] Click **Sign in with Google** — you should be redirected to Google's login page
- [ ] Complete the Google sign-in flow and verify you land back on the app
- [ ] Check **Supabase Dashboard** > **Authentication** > **Users** — your user should appear
- [ ] Click **Sign in with Apple** and repeat the verification
- [ ] Test sign out at `/auth/signout` — verify your session is cleared

### Troubleshooting

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `Redirect URL not in allowed list` | Missing URL in Supabase allowlist | Add `http://localhost:3000/**` to URL Configuration |
| `invalid_grant` on Apple | Expired client secret (>6 months) | Regenerate the `.p8`-signed JWT and update `APPLE_CLIENT_SECRET` |
| `provider is not enabled` | Provider not enabled in Supabase | Authentication > Providers > enable the provider |
| Redirect loop on `/auth/login` | Middleware intercepting `/auth/callback` | Ensure middleware excludes `/auth/*` paths |

